 The plant is subject to the pricing provisions of a State-operated
milk pricing plan which provides for the payment of minimum class
prices for raw milk;

 Milk of a dairy farmer shall not be eligible for diversion unless
at least one day's production of such dairy farmer is
physically received at a pool plant during the month;

 The total quantity of milk diverted by a handler in any month shall
not exceed 50 percent of the total producer milk caused by the
handler to be received at pool plants and diverted;
